      "position": 0,
      "content": "GENERAL INFORMATION FOR ALL MINORS",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "90c86f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "UC Santa Cruz students may complete one or more minors, provided they can finish all required coursework within their maximum enrollment terms and credit limits. Minors are recorded on the official transcript but do not appear on the diploma. Pursuing a minor is optional and should align with a student’s academic interests and career goals. Students do not apply for minors as part of their UC Santa Cruz admission application. Transfer students interested in a minor should reach out to the department that offers it for advising during their first quarter of enrollment.",
      "contentHtml": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">UC Santa Cruz students may complete one or more minors, provided they can finish all required coursework within their maximum enrollment terms and credit limits. Minors are recorded on the official transcript but do not appear on the diploma. Pursuing a minor is optional and should align with a student’s academic interests and career goals.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Students do not apply for minors as part of their UC Santa Cruz admission application. Transfer students interested in a minor should reach out to the department that offers it for advising during their first quarter of enrollment.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "3d766f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralTitle",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 2,
      "content": "Politics Minor",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "b74a7445-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 3,
      "content": "Students majoring in a different program of study may find that a minor in politics is an invaluable addition to their educational plan. Prospective transfer students interested in this minor are encouraged to complete one lower-division course listed in the “Preparation for the Minor” section below before transferring. Please visit the Politics website to learn more about this minor. UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Politics Minor Program Statement",
      "contentHtml": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Students majoring in a different program of study may find that a minor in politics is an invaluable addition to their educational plan.&nbsp;Prospective transfer students interested in this minor are encouraged to complete&nbsp;one lower-division course listed in the “Preparation for the Minor”&nbsp;section below before transferring.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Please visit the </span><a href=\"https://politics.ucsc.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Politics website</a><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"> to learn more about this minor.</span></p><p><a href=\"https://catalog.ucsc.edu/en/current/general-catalog/academic-units/social-sciences-division/politics/politics-minor/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\">UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Politics Minor Program Statement</a></p>"
